cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach for weakly supervised object detection, which involves learning from image-level supervision rather than bounding box annotations. This is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves segmentation, which is another subfield of computer vision (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of their approach on benchmarks, which is related to computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR).
